11/04/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Four soldiers were killed on Monday (10 April), when their Turkish Army helicopter fell on a steel factory in the northwest town of Uzunciftlik. 
Two factory workers were injured. 
The cause of the crash is under investigation.
In other news, local media reported that an unexploded bomb was discovered in a bus in Istanbul on Monday. 
Judicial officials were the apparent target, since the shuttle bus was carrying judges and prosecutors to their office.
Also Monday, one Turkish soldier was killed and another was injured by a landmine in Silvan, near the main city of Diyarbakir. 
The incident occurred amid growing violence and attacks by members of the Kurdistan Workers Party and another terrorist group, the Kurdistan Liberation Hawks. 
(TurkishPress.com, AFP, Reuters - 10/04/06)
